n a genuine turn."}, {"tag": "policy", "text": "Fed reinvestment language still dovish; balance sheet uptick could be a one-off blip."}, {"tag": "positioning", "text": "Panel is split and low-conviction overall, so this level call could reverse quickly on next data."}], "trade": {"legs": [{"instrument": "DGS10", "weight": 0.1}, {"instrument": "DGS2", "weight": 0.05}], "conviction": 0.3, "rationale": "Term premium and balance sheet both flipped away from the prior lower-yield thesis; closing short-duration tilt and moving to a small higher-yield lean given inflation's modest firming."}}
